## Quick Decision Guide

Not sure which one to use? Follow this simple flowchart:

```
Need to exit? → Ask yourself:

├─ Am I in a child process after fork()?
│  ├─ YES → Use os._exit(0) ✓
│  └─ NO  → Continue...
│
├─ Am I in a multiprocessing worker?
│  ├─ YES → Use os._exit(0) ✓
│  └─ NO  → Continue...
│
├─ Do I need cleanup to run?
│  ├─ YES → Use sys.exit(0) ✓
│  └─ NO  → Ask: Why not? (Usually you do!)
│
├─ Am I in the main process?
│  ├─ YES → Use sys.exit(0) ✓
│  └─ NO  → Re-evaluate your design
│
├─ Is this an emergency/deadlock situation?
│  ├─ YES → Maybe os._exit(0), but fix the deadlock!
│  └─ NO  → Use sys.exit(0) ✓
│
└─ DEFAULT → Use sys.exit(0) ✓
```

**Simple rule of thumb:** If you're writing normal application code, use `sys.exit(0)`. Only use `os._exit(0)` if you really know why you need it.

